 Oil field.<br />Source: BusinessPostNigeria  Oil wealth flies above the heads of communities. Just like power lines take power elsewhere leaving us in the dark. Communities farm and endure rotten harvests. Fishers fish, but the fishes are banished by crude. Fishes eat imported iced fish. Communities live by the riverside but may well have been in parched deserts. Riverine communities drink pure water!  , at Oil Field Dialogue held at Ikot Ada Udo To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .